The core concept here is almost exactly like SCP-2362, just with Earth instead of Pluto.

Critiquespace

thesewords


My main problem with this is an entirely mundane phenomenon that is extremely well-documented and entirely reliant on the Earth's composition being what mainstream science says it is: volcanoes.

If the mantle is made of organic materialwhere does magma/lava come from?

I'm also unclear on the exact nature of the place the but then portions of the Site lost to a temporary portal are visible through -1A. The letter from the dead guy also mentions starlight. So are there stars/nebluae (or things that look like them) in the core area?

The but a non-physical aspect isn't ever mentioned, so I'm not sure what that is supposed to mean. It just makes the nature of the thing more confusing.

All in all, currently downvoting because major aspects of the phenomenon are contradictory or are otherwise unclear when it seems it was intended to be clear(er).

(And to be fair, I'm not a fan of the Pluto one either.)










